  "StateDifferential_code": "import torch
import torch.nn as nn

# Define the StateDifferential model

class StateDifferential(nn.Module):

    def __init__(self):
        super(StateDifferential, self).__init__()
        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(1, 64)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(64, 64)
        self.fc3 = nn.Linear(64, 1)

    def forward(self, tumor_size, msi_score, tmb_nonsynonymous, treatment_duration):
        # Tumor size differential
        ts = torch.relu(self.fc1(tumor_size))
        ts = torch.relu(self.fc2(ts))
        ts_diff = self.fc3(ts)

        # MSI score differential
        ms = torch.relu(self.fc1(msi_score))
        ms = torch.relu(self.fc2(ms))
        ms_diff = self.fc3(ms)

        # TMB nonsynonymous differential
        tn = torch.relu(self.fc1(tmb_nonsynonymous))
        tn = torch.relu(self.fc2(tn))
        tn_diff = self.fc3(tn)

        # Treatment duration differential
        td = torch.relu(self.fc1(treatment_duration))
        td = torch.relu(self.fc2(td))
        td_diff = self.fc3(td)

        return ts_diff, ms_diff, tn_diff, td_diff",
  "code_description": "This is a white box model that uses a simple feed-forward neural network to model the state differential of tumor_size, msi_score, tmb_nonsynonymous, and treatment_duration.
